{"format":"tiptap/v1","updatedAt":"2026-06-22T16:12:29.921Z","doc":{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Using subagents in Claude Code transforms a single general-purpose AI assistant into a coordinated team of specialized agents, each operating in its own isolated context window with a focused role, curated toolset, and independent permissions. This architecture is one of the most powerful patterns in Claude Code for building reliable, repeatable, and scalable development workflows."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"What Subagents Are"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"A subagent is a specialized AI assistant within Claude Code defined by a Markdown file with YAML frontmatter. Each subagent runs in its own context window with a custom system prompt, specific tool access, and independent permissions — completely separate from the main conversation. When Claude encounters a task that matches a subagent's description, it automatically delegates to that subagent, which works independently and returns only a summary."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The core benefit is "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"context isolation"},{"type":"text","text":": instead of a single bloated context window accumulating logs, search results, and exploration output, each subagent handles its specific concern and returns only what matters. This also enables "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"cost control"},{"type":"text","text":", since you can route expensive read-heavy tasks to faster, cheaper models like Haiku."}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Built-in Subagents"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Claude Code ships with several pre-configured subagents that activate automatically:"}]},{"type":"table","content